Best Cruise Ships for Families in 2025

By Brooke Franco
  • Share
  • Tweet
  • Pin It
  • Print

Cruising is an excellent way for families to vacation together as it offers a unique combination of relaxation, entertainment, and adventure all in one place. Choosing the right cruise ship can make all the difference for families looking to embark on a memorable journey at sea. With various vessels on the market catering to different interests, budgets, and ages, it can be daunting to find one that best suits your family's preferences. Cruiseline.com is a great starting point for finding the best ships for families. To make it easy, weve compiled a list of the 20 best cruise ships for families in 2025. The rankings are from review scores submitted by community members during the 2024 calendar year who said they traveled as a family. 

 

These top-ranked cruise ships scored the highest for going above and beyond to cater to families, ensuring parents and kids of all ages have an unforgettable experience. Whether you're seeking relaxation, adventure, or a bit of both, these cruise ships offer the perfect setting for family bonding on the high seas.

Based on review data submitted by the Cruiseline.com community, the following are the top 20 cruise ships for families in 2025:
  1. Disney Dream - 4.655
  2. Disney Magic - 4.462
  3. Oasis of the Seas - 4.359
  4. Anthem of the Seas - 4.341
  5. Icon of the Seas - 4.308
  6. Symphony of the Seas - 4.215
  7. Carnival Magic - 4.162
  8. Explorer of the Seas - 4.148
  9. Harmony of the Seas - 4.139
  10. Allure of the Seas - 4.120
  11. Wonder of the Seas - 4.084
  12. Carnival Jubilee - 4.074
  13. Voyager of the Seas - 4.063
  14. Liberty of the Seas - 4.055
  15. Enchantment of the Seas - 4.041
  16. Carnival Panorama - 4.035
  17. Odyssey of the Seas - 4.018
  18. Adventure of the Seas - 4.014
  19. Utopia of the Seas - 4.013
  20. Independence of the Seas - 4.012
 

 

Our Thoughts

Congratulations to Disney Cruise Line, Royal Caribbean, and Carnival Cruise Line for once again sweeping the top 20 spots on this list of the best cruise ships for families! These rankings have several returning cruise ships that made the rankings last year and the debut of several newcomers. 

These three cruise brands are consistently top contenders for creating an unforgettable family vacation. Each line has ships that offer a range of amenities tailored to kids of all ages, ensuring that every family member finds something enjoyable on board. From themed character encounters and cutting-edge entertainment to specialized play areas and supervised youth programs, Disney, Royal Caribbean, and Carnival ships are designed to provide the nonstop fun and excitement travelers crave when seeking a family cruise. 

Next, we will take a closer look at the results of Disney, Royal Caribbean, and Carnival ships in these rankings and share feedback from our community members about these award-winning, family-friendly vessels. 

Disney Cruise Line 

You cant talk about the best in family cruising without Disney Cruise Line being in the mix! Once again Disney was our big leader for the best cruise ships for families of the year, coming in the first two spots on this list for 2025. 

Disney Dream jumped from number three on this same list last year, while Disney Magic retained its ranking at number two. 

Disney Dream and Disney Magic offer a great blend of fun and relaxing spaces designed with family travelers in mind. Members scored the ships highly for attractions like the AquaDuck water coaster, character meets and greets, Disney-inspired shows, family-friendly dining, tremendous kids programs, and other unique entertainment options. Paired with Disney Cruise Lines exceptional service. No matter which Disney ship you choose, they are both top choices for families looking for a magical vacation on the high seas.

Heres what our community members had to say about these top-ranked Disney ships:

Its a great option for families, particularly those with young kids. There were plenty of characters for the kids to meet every day. The special Marvel Day was great, wrote member tcmbondy in a review of Disney Dream

Member amartin500 shared this feedback in a review of Disney Magic, We did this cruise to celebrate my 60th birthday with a few friends. It did not disappoint! We all had a great time and enjoyed the service Disney is known for. Only one day of rain but even then there we ample things to do onboard. Best entertainment options by far of any cruise line we've done

Explore Cruises on Disney Dream

Royal Caribbean

Although it didnt make the top two spots on this list, Royal Caribbean made quite the splash in best ships for families with a whopping 15 vessels making the top 20! Interestingly, eight of these ships made the rankings last year, while seven are newcomers to the rankings. 

Royal Caribbean ships are ideal for families because they offer a wide range of activities and entertainment for all ages. Guests can choose from amenities like water slides, interactive kids' clubs, family-friendly dining, and a mix of stateroom types to accommodate various family sizes. From dedicated kids' playrooms and activity centers to teen discos and age-appropriate offerings, all the Royal Caribbean ships will surely be a hit for families.  No matter their age, kids make new friends and enjoy the activities and dedicated facilities to keep them engaged, entertained, and learning while spending quality time as a family. 

The number three best family ship, Oasis of the Seas, made a big leap up in these rankings for 2025. This ship offers a variety of pools, the Central Park area, Broadway-style shows, and specialized spaces for kids of all ages. Number four, Anthem of the Seas, was just a hundredth of a point behind Oasis for the best family ship. It features a North Star observation capsule and the indoor SeaPlex, both great activities for family bonding. 

Other Royal Caribbean ships making the rankings are the lines newest vessels, Icon of the Seas and Utopia of the Seas. We are not surprised to see both ships make the list as they were designed with family fun in mind. These mega-ships feature some of the world's largest water parks at sea, spacious family suites, and dedicated family-centric neighborhoods. 

Heres what our community members had to say about some of the top-rated Royal Caribbean ships for families: 

Overall a great family trip (ages 19 to 76). We really appreciated the last day at sea to recover from the 15,000 plus steps a day. The ports were great. The ship was great. The food and service was great. Thankful for the opportunity to see all the historic sites with my family, said member VacaPlanner in their review of Oasis of the Seas

Member Cruiser77043433 said this about their cruise on Enchantment of the Seas, My son and I went on this cruise together. We had so much fun and made so many memories. We enjoyed going on a smaller ship and being able to meet the same people over and over again. It truly feels like a more personal experience than on a larger ship. Well definitely be back!

So many activities to keep my kiddos busy! We enjoyed having various dining options with an unpredictable toddler. We enjoyed the main dining room for three nights and the wait staff was great! We frequented Johnny Rockets for breakfast and their staff provided excellent service, said member Cruiser13788310 in their review of sailing onboard Symphony of the Seas

Explore Cruises on Oasis of the Seas

 

 

Carnival Cruise Line

Three Carnival Cruise Line vessels made the list of our top family cruise ships of the year - Carnival Magic, Carnival Jubilee, and Carnival Panorama. Carnival Magic, our number seven best ship of the year for families, is returning from last years rankings, while Jubilee and Panorama are newcomers. 

Dream Class Carnival Magic scored highly for families with its Camp Ocean kids programming and amenities like WaterWorks, the Sports Square, and branded childrens programs in partnership with NASA and Dr. Seuss. 

Carnival Jubilee, an Excel Class Carnival ship, features family fun activities like a ropes course, Build-a-Bear Workshop, Dive-In Movies, and BOLT the roller coaster. As one of the largest and newest ships in the Carnival fleet, it offers extensive stateroom options for family travelers to choose from and dining venues to suit a range of palates for travelers of all ages.  

Number sixteen in the rankings, Carnival Panorama, scored well among members with family features like SkyRide, the Sky Zone, and fun shows like Family Feud Live. This ship underwent a small refurbishment in 2024, adding new amenities that clearly impressed families. 

Heres what community members had to say about these top-ranked Carnival ships for families: 

Carnival's reputation for fun is well-deserved. Our entire family of 17 people has never had such a good all-around cruise experience, shared member DianeN403 in their review of Carnival Panorama

Member Padgitts wrote this great feedback in their review of Carnival Magic, This was our first family cruise and we all said we would do it again. This ship had something for everyone. We also had family photos taken which turned out amazing!

Family group of 14 from age 12 to 65 had a good time. It was a nice way to vacation with something for everyone shared member lilsavesalot in their review of Carnival Jubilee

Explore Cruises on Carnival Magic

Ready to Plan Your Perfect 2025 Family Cruise? 

Whether travelers were sailing on one of these top 20 cruise ships in 2025, or on the hundreds of other ships on the high seas, there is nothing like making memories with your family while visiting destinations worldwide. A round of applause to our award-winning ships from Disney Cruise Line, Royal Caribbean, and Carnival for delivering a memorable cruise experience that left a lasting impression on our community members who traveled with their families this past year! 

Have you recently cruised as a family? Be sure to share your experience by writing a review!

How to Add a Cruise on Shipmate

By Shipmate
  • Share
  • Tweet
  • Pin It
  • Print

Obviously, the first thing youll need to do is to download Shipmate and create a new account. If you havent already, you can do that by clicking here.

 

This is Tutorial #2 in our series. If youre just getting started with Shipmate, please check out: Getting Started with Shipmate Basic Navigation, Creating User Account & Editing Profile.

Youll now be able to add all of your cruises past and future. Keep your entire cruising profile right here in Shipmate. Then you can reminisce on past sailings, or count down to future cruises.

How to Add a Cruise:

  1. Select My Cruises
  2. Click the 'Add a Cruise' button
  3. Select your cruise line
  4. Select your cruise ship
  5. Select the year of your sailing
  6. Select the month of your sailing
  7. Find your specific sailing and click the 'Add Cruise' button

Your selected voyage will now appear on the My Cruises page.

Once you have your future cruise saved, here are some suggestions on how to make the most of your Shipmate App.

  • Check your Roll Call to see who youre sailing with
  • Say Hi to your ship mates in your itinerary chat room
  • See where your ship is right now
  • Check out the weather in your first port of call
  • See what excursions are available for your ports

Have fun exploring!
